author: Reuters
title: DIARY - Today in Washington - Sept 8
text:
ALL TIMES IN EDT/GMT
0600/1000: The National Federation of Independent Business issues Small Business Optimism Index for August.
1000/1400: The Federal Reserve releases its labor market conditions index for August.
1100/1500: The USDA releases weekly U.S. export inspections for grains, oilseeds. (Delayed from Monday due to the Labor Day holiday)
1100/1500: The Treasury Dept. announces weekly sale of 4-week bills (Delayed from Monday due to the Labor Day holiday)
1130/1530: The Treasury Dept holds weekly sale of 3-, 6-month bills. (Delayed from Monday due to the Labor Day holiday)
1300/1700: The Treasury Dept. sells 3-year notes.
1500/1900: The Federal Reserve issues Consumer Installment Credit for July.
1600/2000: The USDA issues weekly Crop Progress report. (Delayed from Monday due to the Labor Day holiday).
